main event: On July 3, 1965, witnesses observed an unidentified object in the sky over Rochester, Minnesota, which was stationary before moving slowly eastward.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 15 minutes, appeared to change shape, and emitted a beam of light for a few seconds., Four witnesses from different locations reported seeing the object, confirming its visibility., The sky was clear with no clouds at the time of the sighting., The object maintained a constant brightness throughout the observation., Witnesses noted its size was comparable to a major planet in the solar system.
sighted object: a strange unidentified object in the sky
witness description: Neighbors and an amateur astronomer observed the object, noting its unique changes in shape and light emission.
